"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139000","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-07-18","<p>The Department’s preferred measure of local government funding is Core Spending Power (CSP). The Department does not publish CSP per capita, but CSP per dwelling is published on the Department’s website:</p><p><a href="https://gbr01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fassets.publishing.service.gov.uk%2Fgovernment%2Fuploads%2Fsystem%2Fuploads%2Fattachment_data%2Ffile%2F774223%2FCore_Spending_Power_Summary.xlsx&amp;data=02%7C01%7CShafi.Khan%40communities.gov.uk%7C36aace8ffc41466ab65f08d70a11ec6f%7Cbf3468109c7d43dea87224a2ef3995a8%7C0%7C0%7C636988944401322346&amp;sdata=lrxpp%2B8K3rtjnIcrV0KEm53vG5YjvB02apPgiX%2FOlY0%3D&amp;reserved=0" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/774223/Core_Spending_Power_Summary.xlsx</a></p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2019-07-18T12:57:44.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139000/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139000/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139000/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-07-15","Local Government Finance: St Helens","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what the per capita funding for St Helens Council is in the current financial year.","false","Biography information for Conor McGinn","St Helens North","Conor McGinn","277214"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139001","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-07-18","<p>The Department does not hold centrally the availability of refuges for victims of domestic violence in St Helens borough and the North West.</p><p>We are currently consulting on the Future Delivery of Support to Victims and their Children in Accommodation-Based Domestic Abuse Services closing on 2 August. The proposals for a statutory duty will require local authorities to convene a Local Partnership Board. Local Partnership Boards will be responsible for robustly assessing need for support for victims and their children in safe accommodation, developing, agreeing and publishing an area-wide Domestic Abuse Strategy, ensuring local commissioning of support services is in line with this to meet the diverse support needs of victims and their children and report to central Government on progress.</p><p>It is our intention that the proposals for a statutory duty, subject to the outcome of the public consultation, will form part of the Domestic Abuse Bill at a later stage.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2019-07-18T13:06:47.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139001/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139001/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139001/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-07-15","Refuges: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what recent assessment he has made of the availability of refuges for victims of domestic violence in (a) St Helens borough and (b) the North West.","false","Biography information for Conor McGinn","St Helens North","Conor McGinn","277215"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139002","Treasury","false","2019-07-18","<p>Milk substitute drinks derived from plants are currently exempt from the soft drinks industry levy. At the time of the introduction of SDIL the Government committed to review this in 2020.</p><p>The government has no plans to extend SDIL at the present time.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2019-07-18T16:59:26.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139002/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139002/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139002/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-07-15","Soft Drinks: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans he has to extend the soft drinks industry levy to milk replacement drinks containing sugar; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","277130"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139003","Treasury","false","2019-07-18","<p>The Government has no plans at this stage to extend the soft drinks industry levy beyond soft drinks. The Government has committed to review the exemption for sugary milk drinks in 2020.</p><p> </p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2019-07-18T16:58:11.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139003/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139003/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139003/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-07-15","Soft Drinks: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans he has to (a) extend the scope of the soft drinks industry levy to other products containing free sugars and (b) increase the rate of the levy.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","277131"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139004","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-07-23","<p>The Government is preparing to consult on amendments to the Transmissible Spongiform Encephalopathies Regulations (2018) in line with changes to EU rules, which would permit the introduction of an optional method of ageing of sheep alternative to dentition.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2019-07-23T15:53:24.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139004/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139004/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139004/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-07-15","Sheep: Transmissible Encephalopathies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to enable the identification of the age of ovine animals other than by the eruption of the permanent incisor under the Transmissible Spongiform Encephalopathies Regulations (2018).","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","277203"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139005","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-07-23","<p>Section 6 of the United Nations Convention on the Law of the Sea Arbitral Tribunal Award (18 March 2015) considers this issue in detail and makes the relevant conclusions.</p>","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison",,"2019-07-23T15:20:25.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139005/answer","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139005/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139005/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-07-15","British Indian Ocean Territory: Sovereignty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to the oral contribution of the Minister of State in Westminster Hall on 3 July, column 584WH, if he will provide a reference to the section of the award of March 2015 of the UN Convention on the Law of the Sea Tribunal which concluded that the Agreement in 1965 to the detachment of the Chagos Archipelago was legally binding.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","277209"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139006","Department for Education","false","2019-07-22","<p>In March 2019, the government announced its decision not to extend maintenance loans to part-time distance learners in the 2019-20 academic year. This was on the grounds that the demand for a loan product aimed at part-time distance learners is unlikely to be high enough to make the introduction of such a loan economically viable.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2019-07-22T15:55:07.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139006/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139006/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139006/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-07-15","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether part-time students studying undergraduate courses using distance learning will be eligible to apply for maintenance loans for the 2019-20 academic year.","false","Biography information for James Frith","Bury North","James Frith","277277"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139007","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-07-19","<p>The Department is assured the supply of Actavis immediate release propranolol tablets is sufficient to meet normal demand. Actavis modified release propranolol capsules are currently unavailable. However, they are expected to be back in stock by the end of July and supplies of generic propranolol capsules are currently available from an alternative manufacturer. The Department does not have information on stock holding of propranolol at a local level.</p>","South Ribble","Seema Kennedy",,"2019-07-19T09:37:33.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139007/answer","Biography information for Seema Kennedy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139007/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139007/answer","South Ribble","Seema Kennedy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139007/answer/previousversion/129853","Biography information for Seema Kennedy","17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-07-15","Propranolol: Somerset","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, if he will make an assessment of the adequacy of supply of the drug Actavis Propranolol in pharmacies in (a) North East Somerset and (b) Somerset.","false","Biography information for Mr Jacob Rees-Mogg","North East Somerset","Mr Jacob Rees-Mogg","277188"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139008","Home Office","false","2019-07-18","<p>We will publish draft guidance on the operation of Knife Crime Prevention Orders (KCPOs) for public consultation shortly.</p><p>During the public consultation period we will be specifically engaging with those who have an interest in the operation of KCPOs, including law enforcement, prosecuting authorities, adult and youth services, Youth Offending Teams and other organisations who have previously expressed an interest. The consultation will be open to all to submit a response and will be accessible on the gov.uk website.</p><p>Final guidance will need to be in place before the pilot scheme can commence. We will be announcing details of the locations for the pilot in due course. The pilot will include the potential for KCPOs, and interim KCPOs, to be applied for in respect of individuals aged under 18, as set out in the Offensive Weapons Act.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins","277273 ; 277274 ; 277275","2019-07-18T16:11:41.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139008/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139008/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139008/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-07-15","Knife Crime Prevention Orders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when he plans to publish draft guidance on the use of Knife Crime Prevention Orders; when the consultation process on that guidance will begin; and for how long it will run.","false","Biography information for Sarah Jones","Croydon Central","Sarah Jones","277272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139009","Home Office","false","2019-07-18","<p>We will publish draft guidance on the operation of Knife Crime Prevention Orders (KCPOs) for public consultation shortly.</p><p>During the public consultation period we will be specifically engaging with those who have an interest in the operation of KCPOs, including law enforcement, prosecuting authorities, adult and youth services, Youth Offending Teams and other organisations who have previously expressed an interest. The consultation will be open to all to submit a response and will be accessible on the gov.uk website.</p><p>Final guidance will need to be in place before the pilot scheme can commence. We will be announcing details of the locations for the pilot in due course. The pilot will include the potential for KCPOs, and interim KCPOs, to be applied for in respect of individuals aged under 18, as set out in the Offensive Weapons Act.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins","277272 ; 277274 ; 277275","2019-07-18T16:11:41.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139009/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139009/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1139009/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-07-15","Knife Crime Prevention Orders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with which stakeholders his Department is engaging to develop guidance on the proposed knife crime prevention orders.","false","Biography information for Sarah Jones","Croydon Central","Sarah Jones","277273"
