"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138449","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-07-18","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave to the hon. Member for Exeter (Rt. Hon Ben Bradshaw MP) on 8 May 2019 to Question <a href="https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2019-06-07/261463/" target="_blank">261463</a>.</p>","South Ribble","Seema Kennedy",,"2019-07-18T09:31:11.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138449/answer","Biography information for Seema Kennedy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138449/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138449/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-07-11","Sexually Transmitted Infections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, if he will increase funding for sexual health services to tackle the increases in cases of syphilis and gonorrhoea in England.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","276266"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138450","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-07-18","<p>The 36 month pre-exposure prophylaxis (PrEP) Impact Trial is scheduled to continue until autumn 2020. Work is now starting to consider future commissioning for PrEP after the trial has ended, which includes consideration of funding options.</p>","South Ribble","Seema Kennedy",,"2019-07-18T09:20:23.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138450/answer","Biography information for Seema Kennedy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138450/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138450/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-07-11","HIV Infection: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps he is taking to find a long-term and sustainable funding package to ensure PrEP is available to all who require it.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","276267"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138451","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-07-16","<p>Solar PV is a UK success story. Over 99% of the UK’s solar PV capacity has been deployed since May 2010, and now provides 13.5GW of renewable electricity. 13.8GW of onshore wind capacity has now also been installed in the UK, enough to power over 7.6 million UK homes. Renewable technologies have an essential part to play in meeting the 2050 net zero emissions commitment as part of a diverse energy system.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2019-07-16T14:43:02.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138451/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138451/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138451/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-07-11","Renewable Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the contribution that (a) rooftop solar, (b) solar farms and (c) onshore wind can make to delivering the 2050 net-zero emissions target; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","276250"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138452","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-07-16","<p>This information is publicly available at:</p><p><a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/811884/ET_6.1.xls" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/811884/ET_6.1.xls</a>.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2019-07-16T14:43:25.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138452/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138452/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138452/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-07-11","Renewable Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what was the capacity of (a) onshore wind and (b) solar PV installed in the UK in (i) 2015, (ii) 2016, (iii) 2017, (iv) 2018, and (v) 2019 to 11 July 2019.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","276251"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138453","Home Office","false","2019-07-16","<p>There is no target for the time taken to make a decision on a claim submitted under the Windrush compensation scheme. We will aim to award compensation as quickly as possible, but the time it will take to process each claim will depend on the complexity of individual cases.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2019-07-16T11:00:46.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138453/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138453/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138453/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-07-11","Immigration: Windrush Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether his Department has a target for the time taken to make a decision on a claim submitted to the Windrush compensation scheme.","false","Biography information for Afzal Khan","Manchester, Gorton","Afzal Khan","276274"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138454","Home Office","false","2019-07-16","<p>The Home Office will publish information on the number of claims submitted, number of claims paid and the overall amount paid out by the scheme in due course as part of our regular reporting to HASC. We do not intend to publish information on the time taken between a claim being submitted and a decision being made on that claim.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2019-07-16T11:05:04.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138454/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138454/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138454/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-07-11","Immigration: Windrush Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether he will publish data on the time taken between someone submitting a claim to the Windrush compensation scheme and a decision being made on that claim.","false","Biography information for Afzal Khan","Manchester, Gorton","Afzal Khan","276275"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138455","Department for International Development","false","2019-07-16","<p>The Department, working with Treasury and other Government departments, is always planning for contingencies to ensure that the UK meets its ODA obligations. The consequences of leaving the European Union without a deal come within this broader contingency planning.</p>","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison",,"2019-07-16T15:54:18.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138455/answer","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138455/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138455/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-07-11","Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps his Department is taking to ensure the UK meets its ODA obligations in the event that the UK leave the European Union without a deal.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Mr Gavin Shuker","276180"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138456","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-07-16","<p>A response from Lord (Tariq) Ahmad of Wimbledon was sent to the hon. Member for Bishop Aukland on 15 July 2019.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2019-07-16T14:08:04.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138456/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138456/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138456/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-07-11","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when he plans to respond to the letter of 18 June 2019 from the hon. Member for Bishop Auckland requesting a meeting with the Minister of State for the Commonwealth.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","276170"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138457","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-07-16","<p>The requested information for part (a) is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>In response to part (b), the number of Households on UC that make use of the Split Payment option is published and can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/</a></p><p>Guidance on how to extract the information required can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started.html" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started.html</a></p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2019-07-16T14:40:51.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138457/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138457/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138457/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-07-11","Universal Credit: Payments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many requests for spilt payments of universal credit have been (a) made and (b) accepted in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Ruth George","High Peak","Ruth George","276271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138458","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-07-16","<p>The requested information is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>However, information on the number of Households on Universal Credit that have an Alternative Payment Arrangement is published and can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/</a></p><p>Guidance on how to extract the information required can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started.html" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started.html</a></p><p />","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2019-07-16T14:49:09.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138458/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138458/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1138458/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-07-11","Universal Credit: Payments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many requests for alternative payment arrangements of universal credit have been (a) made and (b) accepted for (i) twice monthly payments and (b) four twice monthly payments in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Ruth George","High Peak","Ruth George","276272"
